 N4798E Aircraft Health Assistant
# Portfolio project for Cognite Senior Field AI Engineer interview

## Project purpose
Demonstrate understanding of Cognite Data Fusion (CDF) architecture:
- IT/OT/ET data ingestion and contextualization
- Industrial Knowledge Graph
- CAG (Context Augmented Generation) — NOT RAG
- AI agent with function calling over knowledge graph

## Architecture — never deviate from these decisions
- Mock CDF server: Express implementing real CDF REST API endpoints
- Knowledge graph queries: always via @cognite/sdk, never direct JSON reads
- Context assembly: graph traversal only, no vector store, no semantic search
- Agent pattern: ReAct loop with explicit tool calls
- CAG not RAG: context comes from traversing connected graph nodes

## Code standards
- TypeScript strict mode always
- Explicit error handling — no silent failures
- No placeholder functions or TODO comments — implement fully
- Every function must have a JSDoc comment explaining what CDF concept it mirrors
- Log which graph nodes were traversed for every agent query

## Domain knowledge
- Aircraft: 1978 Cessna 172N, N4798E, Lycoming O-320-H2AD engine
- Engine TBO: 2000 hours, currently 1100 SMOH
- Annual inspection required every 12 calendar months
- Oil change interval: 50 hours or 4 months
- Based at KPRC (Prescott, AZ)

## File ownership
- mock-cdf/: Express server implementing CDF API — do not modify architecture
- src/agent/: CAG context assembly and agent loop — core of the project
- src/ingest/: Data pipeline from CSVs to mock CDF
- data/: Generated sample data — do not manually edit